"n.矿脉 【英】 n.矿藏(metal-bearin g vein) n. (位于层次分明的两层岩石之间的)矿藏 【记】读: 露的－从两层岩石中露出来的矿脉! 【参】shale: lode = well: aquifer页岩中间是矿脉 = 源泉中间是含水土层 【记】近于lead 铅→铅矿；load 装载→装矿explode 炸，为了采矿 lode (n.)  original Middle English spelling of load (n.), and custodian of most of the original meaning of ""way, course, carrying."" Differentiation in sense took place 16c. Mining sense of ""vein of metal ore"" is from c.1600, from notion of miners ""following"" it through the rock."
